-- Kellogg stands by 2008 earnings forecast
-- 
-- Thu Sep 4, 2008 12:11pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/04/us-kellogg-outlook-idUSN0427624220080904

 

 CHICAGO  (Reuters) - Kellogg Co ( K.N ) on Thursday stood by its earnings forecast for 2008. 

 In comments at the Lehman Brothers Back-To-School conference, company executives said Kellogg still expects earnings of $2.95 a share to $3.00 a share for the year, the forecast it gave at the end of July. Analysts on average forecast $3.01 a share, according to Reuters Estimates. (Reporting by  Brad Dorfman , editing by Gerald E. McCormick)